---
import Side from '../../layouts/Side.astro';
import profil from '../../data/profil.json';

/* English colophon. NORSK TVILLING: src/pages/kolofon.astro — endre begge.
   Ankeret #tilgjengelighet deles med footeren på begge språk. */

const epost = profil.kontakt.epost;
---

<Side
  lang="en"
  title="Colophon — Stian Glomsrød"
  description="How this site was built: tools, accessibility, privacy and receipts."
>
  <p class="kicker">Colophon</p>
  <h1>How this site was made</h1>
  <p class="dempet">
    The site is built in open dialogue with Claude, and this page documents
    how.
  </p>

  <section aria-labelledby="prosess-tittel">
    <h2 id="prosess-tittel">The process</h2>
    <p class="dempet">
      I started by giving Claude Design good context, so I could iterate on
      and focus the design guide. The third version stuck. I handed the guide
      over to Claude Code, which worked with skills I have built for it:
      /prd, /norwegian-software-guardrails and /secure-dev-guardrails.
    </p>
    <p class="dempet">
      Before anything was built, we measured the old site: Lighthouse, an
      accessibility check and screenshots at three screen widths. The numbers
      live in the repo and become the baseline for comparison at launch.
    </p>
    <p class="dempet">
      The building itself happens in sessions with Claude Code, in loops
      against the done-criteria (see <a href="/en/how-i-work">how I work</a>).
      Checks run automatically before every build, decisions are logged with
      a date and a rollback command, and everything is verified in a running
      preview before it enters the history. Along the way we changed design
      direction completely. That sits in the log as a documented decision,
      not as an overwrite.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section aria-labelledby="stack-tittel">
    <h2 id="stack-tittel">Stack and data</h2>
    <p class="dempet">
      Astro, with a small React island for the game in
      <a href="/en/sandbox">/sandbox</a>, hosted on Vercel. The fonts Hanken
      Grotesk, Atkinson Hyperlegible and Anybody are self-hosted and
      subsetted, all under the SIL Open Font License. The live numbers on the
      front page come from a data file in the repo and GitHub's API, with a
      static reserve if the fetch fails.
    </p>
    <p class="dempet">
      Lighthouse numbers and the full build history will be published here at
      launch.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="tilgjengelighet" aria-labelledby="uu-tittel">
    <h2 id="uu-tittel">Accessibility</h2>
    <p class="dempet">
      The target is WCAG 2.1 AA. The statement will be published together
      with the test log once the site is complete.
    </p>
  </section>
  <section id="personvern" aria-labelledby="pv-tittel">
    <h2 id="pv-tittel">Privacy</h2>
    <p class="dempet">
      The site sets no cookies and has no tracking or analytics. Your choices
      for theme and colour hue are stored only locally in your own browser,
      and never leave your machine.
    </p>
    <p class="dempet">
      If you use the contact form, your name, email address and message are
      forwarded to me as an email. Nothing is stored in any database. The
      basis for the processing is that you chose to get in touch, and the
      details are used only to reply to you.
    </p>
    <p class="dempet">
      Two data processors are involved: Vercel hosts the site, and Resend
      delivers the email from the form. Both process data within the EU/EEA.
      If you want to see what I have, or have it deleted, just send an email
      to <a href={`mailto:${epost}`}>{epost}</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</Side>

<style>
  .kicker {
    font-family: var(--font-hd);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: var(--tekst-label);
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--dempet);
    margin: var(--s-7) 0 var(--s-2);
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: var(--tekst-tittel);
    margin: 0 0 var(--s-3);
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 18px;
    margin: var(--s-6) 0 var(--s-2);
  }

  .dempet {
    color: var(--dempet);
    max-width: 68ch;
  }
</style>
